# in-silico-PCR
This program takes a target DNA sequence and two primers sequences as an input.<BR/>
Output is :<BR/>
&nbsp;    - The number and position of homologous sequences in the target sequence for each primer<BR/>
&nbsp;    - If the two primers match the target sequence at only one position, additional output is :<BR/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;            - length of amplicon<BR/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;            - sequence of amplicon<BR/>
&nbsp;&nbsp;            - position of amplicon on target sequence<BR/>
<BR/>
The following sequences can be used as positive control :<BR/><BR/>
    target = ""<BR/><BR/>
    primerF = "CACACGGAGTTTCCTCCCTA"<BR/><BR/>
    primerR = "TCTTCAGGTCTGCCAACAGG"<BR/>
